## 7. Annotated Disposition

### 7.1 Thesis Structure (Annotated)

**Ch1: Introduction** — Context, problem statement, objective: reusable personality-adaptive architecture via Stress Micro-Coach. **Ch2: Literature Review** — Personality-adaptive dialogue, Zurich Model, stress assessment, evaluation methodologies; gaps and hypotheses. **Ch3: Methodology** — N8N pipeline; Personality Adapter (OCEAN+EMA detection, Zurich regulation, quote-and-bound generation); stress assessment; privacy; database schema. **Ch4: Implementation** — Workflow details, contracts, simulation protocols (Type A/B/Mixed), evaluator setup, metrics. **Ch5: Results** — Detection validity, regulation effectiveness, tone/relevance/needs outcomes vs. baseline, safety, ablations, costs. **Ch6: Discussion** — Interpretation, relation to prior work, validity threats, ethics, generalization. **Ch7: Conclusion** — Contributions, limitations, future research roadmap. **Appendices** — Prompts, schemas, workflow JSON, rubrics, analysis code, reproducibility checklist.

### 7.2 Thesis Extension Framework

**Enhancements:** Temporal smoothing (EMA), response verification, PostgreSQL persistence. **Human Validation:** Participant studies with ethical oversight, consent, professional supervision; generalizability assessment. **Advanced Evaluation:** Human evaluators + automated scoring; inter-rater reliability; longitudinal assessment. **Application Integration:** System integration across domains; adaptive decision support; escalation protocols. **Hybrid Memory-Personality Architecture:** Integrate personality-aware regulation with mem0/LangChain Memory for combined factual recall + motivational adaptation; explore: (i) memory retrieval augmenting detection, (ii) personality profiles as indexing dimensions, (iii) coordinated updates. **Multimodal Extensions:** Voice, facial, physiological monitoring (future); privacy-evaluated.

### 7.3 Publication and Dissemination Strategy

**Academic:** Submit to CHI, AAAI, JPSP, TOCHI, CSCW. **Open Source:** N8N workflow, evaluation framework, analysis tools. **Industry:** Present at technology, education, interaction conferences. **Policy:** Contribute to AI regulatory frameworks with evidence-based guidance.

