### 9.2 Detailed Activity Breakdown

**Weeks 1-2 (Foundation):** Literature review (personality-aware dialogue, Zurich Model, evaluation methodologies); RQ refinement with supervisors; N8N setup; Docker environment; LLM API access; workflow prototyping.

**Weeks 3-4 (Implementation):** N8N workflow nodes; LLM API integration; personality detection prompts (JSON schema); regulation directive mapping; prompt engineering (detection, generation, evaluation); A/B testing; logging system; data export; version control; testing framework.

**Weeks 5-6 (Validation):** Type A/B simulations; multi-instance data collection; performance monitoring; QA checks; LLM evaluator deployment; multiple runs; bias control (randomization, blinding); descriptive stats; comparative analysis; effect sizes; significance testing.

**Week 7 (Analysis):** Statistical analysis; qualitative conversation analysis; comparison with Devdas (2025); visualization (charts, diagrams, confidence intervals); limitation and risk analysis; validity threats; recommendations.

**Week 8 (Documentation):** PMT integration; appendix assembly; APA references; QA review; peer review submission; feedback integration; technical validation.

**Week 9 (Finalization):** Revisions (supervisor, peer feedback); proofreading; reference validation; thesis proposal outline; ethical approvals planning; thesis timeline; conference presentation; demonstration materials; lessons learned.

